1
00:00:34,663 --> 00:00:35,664
Hyung...

2
00:00:35,664 --> 00:00:37,791
I'm doing very well.

3
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:39,918
Hey, did you hear about that?

4
00:00:39,918 --> 00:00:40,502
What?

5
00:00:40,502 --> 00:00:41,753
No, I mean yesterday...

6
00:00:43,421 --> 00:00:44,506
Is he completely out of his mind?

7
00:00:44,506 --> 00:00:46,508
I'm serious, I really had no idea.

8
00:00:51,972 --> 00:00:53,723
Hello.

9
00:01:00,063 --> 00:01:01,731
Still hasn't been fired yet?

10
00:01:02,482 --> 00:01:05,777
I know, right? Talk about thick-skinned.

11
00:01:11,491 --> 00:01:13,451
I'm eating well,

12
00:01:13,451 --> 00:01:15,578
and getting along with the people at work.

13
00:01:17,163 --> 00:01:18,957
I even wore the spring clothes you bought me.

14
00:01:21,418 --> 00:01:23,795
The cherry blossoms outside have bloomed beautifully.

15
00:01:24,629 --> 00:01:25,797
Next year, definitely with you, hyung,

16
00:01:25,797 --> 00:01:28,299
I hope we can see this view together.

17
00:01:35,807 --> 00:01:36,933
Team Leader.

18
00:01:38,643 --> 00:01:40,186
You haven't had breakfast yet, right?

19
00:01:40,186 --> 00:01:41,688
Today it's...

20
00:01:44,232 --> 00:01:45,358
tuna mayo.

21
00:01:49,320 --> 00:01:50,071
Hey...

22
00:01:51,489 --> 00:01:52,699
What is it?

23
00:01:52,699 --> 00:01:53,533
What's wrong with him?

24
00:02:00,457 --> 00:02:02,167
You don't have to do this for me.

25
00:02:04,294 --> 00:02:05,462
Come on...

26
00:02:05,462 --> 00:02:07,422
You still need to eat.

27
00:02:09,549 --> 00:02:10,508
Here you go.

28
00:02:12,552 --> 00:02:13,553
Make sure you do.

29
00:02:33,573 --> 00:02:35,784
Regarding the misappropriation of travel expenses for foreign buyers.

30
00:02:35,784 --> 00:02:37,243
Please explain yourself.

31
00:02:38,369 --> 00:02:39,954
The entertainment expenses were processed normally,

32
00:02:39,954 --> 00:02:40,872
and the receipts were also submitted...

33
00:02:40,872 --> 00:02:42,040
As for the receipts...

34
00:02:42,040 --> 00:02:43,875
We received a tip that they were forged.

35
00:02:45,210 --> 00:02:46,461
The dates on twenty of those receipts

36
00:02:46,461 --> 00:02:48,129
do not match the buyer's business trip schedule.

37
00:02:49,589 --> 00:02:51,633
That was a mistake made by the Management Support Department.

38
00:02:51,633 --> 00:02:52,926
Please check the original data...

39
00:02:55,595 --> 00:02:57,305
The original data...

40
00:02:57,305 --> 00:02:59,265
has already been deleted.

41
00:03:02,602 --> 00:03:05,146
The final result will be announced next week.

42
00:03:06,356 --> 00:03:07,649
You may leave.

43
00:03:20,286 --> 00:03:22,038
So young, and already doing things like this...

44
00:03:24,332 --> 00:03:25,458
Then again...

45
00:03:25,458 --> 00:03:26,501
Since he is in Managing Director Seo Young-woo's line,

46
00:03:26,501 --> 00:03:28,670
there are rumors he's just a scapegoat, but...

47
00:03:30,421 --> 00:03:31,714
Who cares?

48
00:03:32,173 --> 00:03:35,176
Without any evidence, who would believe him anyway?

49
00:03:53,945 --> 00:03:55,947
Hyung, don't worry about me.

50
00:03:55,947 --> 00:03:57,699
Because I believe in you.

51
00:04:07,709 --> 00:04:09,419
Don't you feel it's unfair?

52
00:04:10,503 --> 00:04:11,588
I know everything.

53
00:04:11,588 --> 00:04:13,715
That it wasn't you who did it.

54
00:04:14,257 --> 00:04:15,592
If you have a sin,

55
00:04:15,592 --> 00:04:17,385
it is none other than the sin

56
00:04:17,385 --> 00:04:18,386
of loving Managing Director Seo Young-woo.

57
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:19,804
Who are you?

58
00:04:20,013 --> 00:04:21,014
Me?

59
00:04:22,724 --> 00:04:25,435
Someone who can help you.

60
00:04:25,435 --> 00:04:26,895
Check the attachment.

61
00:04:33,067 --> 00:04:35,987
Change the receipt dates for Kwon Do-young.

62
00:04:36,654 --> 00:04:38,698
Delete the originals from the server.

63
00:04:39,824 --> 00:04:41,868
This is Managing Director Seo Young-woo's instruction.

64
00:04:50,877 --> 00:04:52,003
What is this?

65
00:04:52,003 --> 00:04:53,755
Here is a recording file.

66
00:04:55,924 --> 00:04:58,593
Change the receipt dates for Kwon Do-young.

67
00:04:59,802 --> 00:05:01,346
Delete the originals from the server.

68
00:05:11,856 --> 00:05:13,399
This...

69
00:05:13,399 --> 00:05:15,318
Where did you get this?

70
00:05:16,861 --> 00:05:18,905
The source...

71
00:05:20,531 --> 00:05:22,492
cannot be revealed.

72
00:05:30,917 --> 00:05:32,502
Yes, I understand.

73
00:05:33,461 --> 00:05:34,379
I will ask the Management Support Department

74
00:05:34,379 --> 00:05:36,506
to recover the original server.

75
00:05:41,135 --> 00:05:42,345
Thank you.

76
00:06:04,075 --> 00:06:05,493
Who are you?

77
00:06:05,952 --> 00:06:07,578
Let's meet and talk.

78
00:06:19,507 --> 00:06:21,509
[The number you have dialed is currently unavailable.]

79
00:06:22,593 --> 00:06:24,762
Seriously, are they messing with me?

80
00:06:31,436 --> 00:06:32,312
Team Leader.

81
00:06:34,689 --> 00:06:35,732
Seo Ji-hyuk?

82
00:06:37,692 --> 00:06:39,193
What are you doing here?

83
00:06:40,486 --> 00:06:41,988
I'm heading home.

84
00:06:42,739 --> 00:06:43,948
That car over there is mine.

85
00:06:47,493 --> 00:06:48,953
But what about you, Team Leader?

86
00:06:49,245 --> 00:06:50,705
What brings you here?

87
00:06:53,374 --> 00:06:55,084
I'm about to leave too.

88
00:06:56,461 --> 00:06:57,712
But this is the parking lot,

89
00:06:58,713 --> 00:07:00,923
and you don't usually drive to work, Team Leader.

90
00:07:01,966 --> 00:07:03,134
Ah...

91
00:07:03,468 --> 00:07:04,427
I have an appointment,

92
00:07:04,427 --> 00:07:06,429
so they're picking me up here.

93
00:07:07,347 --> 00:07:09,223
Ah, I see.

94
00:07:10,725 --> 00:07:12,435
Oh, I heard about it.

95
00:07:13,311 --> 00:07:14,645
That everything was resolved.

96
00:07:15,188 --> 00:07:16,147
Congratulations.

97
00:07:16,147 --> 00:07:16,647
Ah...

98
00:07:16,647 --> 00:07:18,149
Yeah, thanks.

99
00:07:19,192 --> 00:07:20,318
See you tomorrow.

100
00:07:21,861 --> 00:07:24,238
But why did they leave out the Managing Director?

101
00:07:29,202 --> 00:07:30,161
What?

102
00:07:32,830 --> 00:07:33,664
Pardon?

103
00:07:39,504 --> 00:07:41,047
What did you just say?

104
00:07:42,465 --> 00:07:44,258
I didn't say anything?

105
00:07:50,765 --> 00:07:52,558
Well, I'll be going now.

106
00:07:56,687 --> 00:07:57,939
See you tomorrow.

107
00:08:25,883 --> 00:08:27,135
Today, someone who seems to know about our relationship...

108
00:08:27,135 --> 00:08:29,470
contacted me.

109
00:08:29,846 --> 00:08:30,805
They said that you, hyung,

110
00:08:30,805 --> 00:08:33,141
framed me for everything.

111
00:08:34,016 --> 00:08:35,226
But you know what?

112
00:08:35,726 --> 00:08:37,270
I don't believe them.

113
00:08:37,854 --> 00:08:39,105
So please wake up soon

114
00:08:39,105 --> 00:08:40,356
and tell me

115
00:08:40,356 --> 00:08:41,315
that it's all a misunderstanding.

116
00:08:42,191 --> 00:08:44,110
You must be going through the hardest time, hyung,

117
00:08:44,861 --> 00:08:46,487
so I'm sorry for telling you this.

118
00:08:47,655 --> 00:08:48,739
I miss you.

119
00:08:49,407 --> 00:08:50,450
Fool.

120
00:08:52,285 --> 00:08:54,495
What a romance of the century.

121
00:08:56,956 --> 00:08:57,832
Young Master.

122
00:08:58,666 --> 00:09:00,751
But why did you change your mind?

123
00:09:01,836 --> 00:09:04,088
Weren't you planning to get rid of everyone

124
00:09:04,088 --> 00:09:06,007
who was on Managing Director Seo Young-woo's side?

125
00:09:07,884 --> 00:09:09,510
I was.

126
00:09:11,220 --> 00:09:12,972
But I changed my mind.

127
00:09:19,562 --> 00:09:21,314
Because I saw someone crying.

128
00:09:37,872 --> 00:09:40,124
I've never seen a man cry so beautifully before.

129
00:09:42,877 --> 00:09:43,961
To the point where I realized

130
00:09:44,504 --> 00:09:47,548
that my brother didn't just keep him around for nothing.

131
00:09:50,927 --> 00:09:53,262
By the way, how is my brother doing?

132
00:09:54,096 --> 00:09:56,182
Well, he is still...

133
00:09:56,182 --> 00:09:58,100
unconscious.

134
00:10:00,019 --> 00:10:01,562
I see...

135
00:10:01,562 --> 00:10:03,064
Seo Young-woo.

136
00:10:03,397 --> 00:10:05,399
Just stay exactly like that.

137
00:10:07,235 --> 00:10:09,987
Because there is nothing left for you in this company anymore.
